gw.api.web.productmodel

Class ProductModelSyncIssue

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.web.productmodel.ProductModelSyncIssue
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConditionIssueBase, CoverageIssueBase, CovTermIssueBase, DataModelSyncIssue, DisplayOnlyProductModelSyncIssue, ExclusionIssueBase, MissingPolicyLineIssue, ModifierIssueBase, QuestionIssueBase, RateFactorIssueBase, RetiredTypekeyValueIssue, UnavailableOfferingIssue, UnavailableOptionValueIssue, UnavailablePackageValueIssue, UnavailablePolicyLineIssue, UnavailablePolicyTermIssue, UnavailableTypekeyValueIssue

    public abstract class ProductModelSyncIssue
extends java.lang.Object
    Base class representing an availability-related issue discovered when syncing the data against the product model. There is a concrete subclass of ProductModelSyncIssue for every possible issue type. Every issue has methods to get out the display name of the entity associated with the issue, such as the Coverable or Modifiable entity in question, and to "fix" the issue.

    • Method Detail

      • isFixed

        public boolean isFixed()
        Indicates whether or not the fixIssue() method has been called. Note that this doesn't actually check to see if the underlying issue has been resolved, so if fixIssue() has not been called but the underlying issue has been fixed through some other path this method will still return false.
        Returns:
        true if fixIssue() has been called, false otherwise

      • fixIssue

        public void fixIssue(BundleProvider bundle)
        Fixes this in the provided bundle. The bundle needs to be passed in because, due to UI issues, the entity associated with the issue may no longer be in the right bundle. This method will do nothing if the issue is already fixed, and otherwise will take an action depending on the issue subtype.
        Parameters:
        bundle - BundleProvider for the bundle in which to fix the issue

      • getOwningEntityDisplayName

        public java.lang.String getOwningEntityDisplayName()
        Returns then name of the entity that this issue applies to. For coverage-related issues this will be the DisplayName of the Coverable object, while for modifier-related issues this will be the DisplayName of the Modifiable object the modifier is attached to.
        Returns:
        the display name of the entity this issue is related to

      • getOwningEntitySliceDate

        public java.util.Date getOwningEntitySliceDate()
        Returns the slice date of the owning entity, but only in the case that it is part of an out of sequence change. If the owning entity is not sliced or is not part of an OOS change, this method will return null.
        Returns:
        the slice date if the owning entity is part of an OOS change, null otherwise
